[Baseline cubic and quartic stochastic symbols]\label{prop:cubic-quartic-baseline}
Assume $\alpha>3/4$. The cubic resonant symbols
\begin{equation*}
\Gamma_1=V_2\circ\Psi_1,
\qquad
\Gamma_2=V_1\circ\Psi_2
\end{equation*}
admit canonical cutoff limits as stochastic distributions with baseline regularity
\begin{equation}\label{eq:gamma-baseline}
\Gamma_i\in C_T\mathcal{C}^{4\alpha-9/2-}.
\end{equation}
The nonzero-chaos part of $V_1V_2$ admits a canonical baseline lift in
\begin{equation}\label{eq:vv-nonzero-baseline}
(V_1V_2)^{\neq 0}\in C_T\mathcal{C}^{6\alpha-6-}.
\end{equation}
Moreover, the zero-chaos part of $V_1V_2$ is a deterministic scalar process; under the speed-separated double Volterra estimate its dyadic shell is $N^{6-7\alpha+}$, so it converges in $C_T$ for $\alpha>6/7$.

