[Conditional deterministic closure]\label{thm:conditional-closure-intro}
Assume the fractional periodic Klein--Gordon Strichartz package of Assumption \ref{ass:strichartz}. Assume that the enhanced stochastic data satisfy Theorem \ref{thm:baseline-lift}, Proposition \ref{prop:cubic-quartic-baseline}, Theorem \ref{thm:operator-main}, and Proposition \ref{prop:mid-completion}. Assume in addition that the pure stochastic forcing is available in the source norm
\begin{equation}\label{eq:source-hyp-intro}
F^V:=\Psi_1V_2+\Psi_2V_1+V_1V_2\in C_TH^{s_2-\alpha},
\end{equation}
and that the parameters $(\alpha,s_1,s_2,\theta)$ satisfy the closure conditions listed in Definition \ref{def:admissible}. Then the paracontrolled system for the remainder variables $(X_1,X_2,Y_1,Y_2)$ is locally well posed in
\begin{equation*}
(X_T^{s_1})^2\times (Y_T^{s_2})^2.
\end{equation*}
The solution map is locally Lipschitz in the enhanced-data norms.

[Sharpness of the same-color shell]\label{prop:sharpness}
There exist a fixed low output frequency $q$, a conic sector of the resonant shell, and a smooth time profile $w(q,t)$ supported only at that frequency such that the leading same-color deterministic contraction on the dyadic shell $|\ell|\sim N$ satisfies
\begin{equation}\label{eq:sharpness}
\|D_N^{i;j}w\|_{C_TH^{s_2-\alpha}}\gtrsim N^{3-4\alpha}
\end{equation}
up to strictly lower-order terms. Consequently $\alpha=3/4$ is logarithmically critical for the deterministic contraction channel.

