[Volterra oscillation estimate]\label{lem:volterra}
Let $a\in C^1([0,T])$ and let $|\Phi|\gtrsim N^\alpha$. Then
\begin{equation}\label{eq:volterra-est}
\sup_{0\le t\le T}
\Bigl|\int_0^t a(s)e^{\mathrm{i}(t-s)\Phi}\,ds\Bigr|
\lesssim N^{-\alpha}\bigl(\|a\|_{L^\infty_T}+\|\partial_t a\|_{L^\infty_T}\bigr).
\end{equation}
The same bound holds with $\sin((t-s)\Phi)$ or $\cos((t-s)\Phi)$ in place of the exponential.

