[Same-color deterministic contraction]\label{prop:det-contraction}
Let $i\neq j$. Define
\begin{equation}\label{eq:DN-operator}
(\mathcal D_N^{i;j}w)_q(t)=\int_0^t D_N^{i;j}(q;t,s)\widehat w(q,s)\,ds.
\end{equation}
Then
\begin{equation}\label{eq:DN-bound}
\|\mathcal D_N^{i;j}w\|_{C_TH^{s_2-\alpha}}
\lesssim_T
\Bigl(N^{3-4\alpha}+N^{3-4\alpha+\theta(s_2+\varepsilon)}\Bigr)
\bigl(\|w\|_{C_TL^2}+\|\partial_t w\|_{C_TH^{-\alpha-\varepsilon}}\bigr).
\end{equation}
Consequently $\sum_N\mathcal D_N^{i;j}$ converges in $\mathcal L(E_T,C_TH^{s_2-\alpha})$ whenever the second condition in \eqref{eq:operator-cond-main} holds.

