[No singular centering for mixed random operators]\label{thm:no-singular-centering}
Assume \eqref{eq:operator-cond-main}. Then each strongly low--high mixed random operator has a cutoff limit as a pathwise bounded operator
\begin{equation*}
E_T\to C_TH^{s_2-\alpha}.
\end{equation*}
Cross-color blocks are automatically centered by independence. Same-color blocks decompose as
\begin{equation*}
T^{i;j,j}=\mathcal D^{i;j}+\mathcal B^{i;j,j},
\end{equation*}
where $\mathcal D^{i;j}$ is a finite speed-separated deterministic Volterra multiplier and $\mathcal B^{i;j,j}$ is a centered pathwise random operator. No divergent random-operator counterterm is subtracted.

[Fractional periodic Klein--Gordon Strichartz package]\label{ass:strichartz}
For $0<T\le 1$ and $i=1,2$, the Duhamel operator $I_i$ satisfies the inhomogeneous estimates required for the norms
\begin{equation}\label{eq:X-space}
\|X\|_{X_T^{s_1}}
:=\|X\|_{C_TH^{s_1}}+\|\partial_tX\|_{C_TH^{s_1-\alpha}}+\|X\|_{L_T^8W^{s_1-\alpha/4,8/3}},
\end{equation}
\begin{equation}\label{eq:Y-space}
\|Y\|_{Y_T^{s_2}}
:=\|Y\|_{C_TH^{s_2}}+\|\partial_tY\|_{C_TH^{s_2-\alpha}}+\|Y\|_{L_T^4W^{s_2-\alpha/2,4}},
\end{equation}
with a positive local-time factor $T^\delta$ in the nonlinear estimates used below.

