[Safe bookkeeping range]\label{cor:safe-range}
Assume the baseline value $\rho_V=3\alpha-3-$ and no improvement beyond the naive low--high estimate for the $X$-equation. If
\begin{equation*}
\alpha>\frac{12}{13},
\end{equation*}
then one can choose $0<s_1<s_2$ and $0<\theta<1$ satisfying Definition \ref{def:admissible}. Thus, once a source-level or primitive-level cubic forcing enhancement is available, the conservative deterministic closure is consistent in this range.

